## üé® DESIGN SYSTEM GUIDELINES (All Pages)

To ensure consistency across all 5 pages, follow these guidelines:

### Color Palette
- **Primary Background**: `#0a0e1a` or `#0f1419` (deep space black)
- **Secondary Background**: `#1a1f2e` (slightly lighter)
- **Accent Primary**: `#00d4ff` (electric cyan)
- **Accent Secondary**: `#9d4edd` (electric purple)
- **Accent Tertiary**: `#3a86ff` (bright blue)
- **Text Primary**: `#ffffff` (white)
- **Text Secondary**: `#b0b9c4` (light gray)
- **Neon Glow**: Cyan or purple with low opacity blur

### Typography
- **Headline Font**: Choose a distinctive, bold display font (avoid Inter/Roboto). Examples:
  - "Space Mono" (futuristic, monospace feel)
  - "Orbitron" (geometric, cyberpunk)
  - "Audiowide" (sci-fi inspired)
  - "JetBrains Mono" (tech-forward)
- **Body Font**: Clean, highly readable (e.g., "Roboto", "Inter", or similar)
- **Sizes**: Large h1 (3-4rem), h2 (2-2.5rem), h3 (1.5rem), body (1rem)

### Visual Effects
- **Glassmorphism**: `backdrop-filter: blur(10px)`, `background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05)`, border with subtle gradient
- **Glowing Borders**: `box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.5)`
- **Neon Text Glow**: `text-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(157, 78, 221, 0.8)`
- **Smooth Transitions**: CSS transitions on hover/click (200-300ms ease-out)
- **Micro-animations**: Use Anime.js for staggered reveals, particle effects, parallax scrolling

### Responsive Design
- Desktop: Full width, multi-column layouts
- Tablet: 2-column grids, adjusted spacing
- Mobile: Single column, touch-friendly buttons, optimized for readability

### Navigation
- Sticky header with 4 main nav buttons: ORGANIZATION | TOURNAMENTS | ROSTER | JOIN US
- Logo/branding on left
- Optional: User profile icon on right (if logged in)
- Mobile: Hamburger menu (optional, can collapse nav into sidebar)

---

## üöÄ IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

### Routing Structure in Next.js
```
app/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx              # HOME (/)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ organization/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx          # ORGANIZATION (/organization)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tournaments/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx          # TOURNAMENTS (/tournaments)
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ [id]/
‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx      # Individual tournament details (/tournament/[id]) [KEEP EXISTING]
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ roster/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx          # ROSTER (/roster)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ join-us/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx          # JOIN US (/join-us)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ api/                  # Existing API routes (no changes)
```

### Data Fetching
- **Home Page**: Fetch featured tournaments, roster teaser, org highlights
- **Organization Page**: Static content + fetch org data (if stored in DB)
- **Tournaments Page**: Fetch all tournaments, apply filters/sorts
- **Roster Page**: Fetch all players + teams, apply filters/sorts
- **Join Us Page**: Static content + form submission to DB

### Shared Components
- **Header/Navigation**: Single reusable component across all pages
- **Footer**: Shared footer component
- **GlassmorphicCard**: Reusable card component with glassmorphic styling
- **Animations**: Centralized Anime.js animation library

---

## ‚ú® Summary

This 5-page structure transforms your single-page layout into a **modular, professional, and scalable platform**. Each page has a clear purpose, maintains consistent branding, and provides a distinct user experience while remaining cohesive through the cyberpunk-noir aesthetic.

Start with **Design Prompts** above for each page, then implement page-by-page with the shared design system to ensure unity across the platform.

